column2: Somewhat windy out of the NW.  Very little if any algae.
Clear sky- light breeze- slight chop on the water.
Previous week 2-3" of rain.  Sunny summer like day with light SW breeze.
Clear - zero clouds- windy- choppy waters.
Mostly cloudy- several days of below normal temps and precipitation.
Clear day- calm. Had several days upper 80s - low 90s.
very windy- high waves- unable to hold anchor- water temp only to 12'
partly sunny- warm- calm partly sunny- warm- calm
clear blue sky- cool- light wind
clear- sunny- cool- calm winds- temps in the 40s last night

Clear- sunny- breezy and warm day.
Sunny and very windy.  Too windy to do water temperature.
Along with my wife- Pat Barofsky- we noted a mostly cloudy day with slight breeze.
Along with Pat Barofsky noted clear sky- slight breeze.
Along with Pat Barofsky noted breezy- hazy- sunny sky.
sunny-hazy- several days of high temps
